The House agreed to suspend the rules and pass the following measures:<P/>H.R. 3537, amended, to amend the Controlled Substances Act to clarify how controlled substance analogues are to be regulated, by a 2/3 yea-and-nay vote of 258 yeas to 101 nays, Roll No. 557;<P/>Agreed to amend the title so as to read: ``To amend the Controlled Substances Act to add certain synthetic substances to schedule I, and for other purposes.''
